<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="28" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,870,2013]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">
[TL: Peoples 
<collectingCountry box="[740,946,1663,1689]" name="Taiwan" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Republic of China</collectingCountry>
, NW Xinjiang, Yining, Sibo, Ili Valley]. The locality data label (see 
<figureCitation box="[411,497,1699,1725]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1857,1881]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,560,1833]" captionTargetId="figure-219@4.[151,1436,560,1833]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. 7, Lectotype of Melitaea phoebe sibina Alphéraky, 1881. 8, Melitaea phoebe ab. tatara Krulikovsky, 1891. 9, Lectotype of Melitaea phoebe ornata Christoph, 1893. 10, Lectotype of Melitaea phoebe uralensis Krulikovsky, 1897 (= ufensis Krulikovsky 1902). 11, Lectotype of Melitaea phoebe var. tungusa Herz, 1899. Figs 7, 9, 11 © V.A. Lukhtanov. Figs 8, 10 © expired. A = upperside, B = underside, C = labels on specimen pin." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577635" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577635/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Fig. 7C</figureCitation>
) has the location in Russian ‘Kuldscha, Kainak’, since this was Russian territory in 1879)]; for some considerable time this taxon has been given specific status, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alpheraky" authorityYear="1881" box="[1028,1201,1735,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibina">
<emphasis box="[1028,1201,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Melitaea sibina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, for example: Grum- Grshimailo, 1895: 291, 
<bibRefCitation author="Schultz, O." box="[422,615,1771,1797]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" pagination="90 - 92" refId="ref11069" refString="Schultz, O. (1908) Ueber einige Farbungs- und Zeichnungs- anomalien aus dem Genus Melitaea F. Entomologische Zeitschrift, 22, 90 - 92." type="journal article" year="1908">Schultz 1908: 91</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Higgins, L. G." box="[672,893,1771,1797]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" pagination="175 - 365" refId="ref9372" refString="Higgins, L. G. (1941) An illustrated catalogue of the Palearctic Melitaea (Lep. Rhopalocera). Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London, 91, 175 - 365. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1941. tb 01045. x" type="journal article" year="1941">Higgins, 1941: 347</bibRefCitation>
. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Toth, J. P. &amp; Varga, Z." box="[1022,1260,1771,1797]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" pagination="258 - 268" refId="ref11248" refString="Toth, J. P. &amp; Varga, Z. (2011) Inter- and intraspecific variation in the genitalia of the ' Melitaea phoebe group' (Lepidoptera. Nymphalidae). Zoologischer Anzeiger, 250, 258 - 268. [6 pp. of Appendix with key and figures of genitalia only present in the on-line version, www. sciencedirect. com] https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. jcz. 2011.05.002" type="book chapter" year="2011">Tóth &amp; Varga (2011)</bibRefCitation>
were unable to separate 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alpheraky" authorityYear="1881" box="[249,354,1807,1833]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibina">
<emphasis box="[249,354,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">M. sibina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Denis &amp; Schiffermuller" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[422,540,1807,1833]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoebe">
<emphasis box="[422,540,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">M. phoebe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
using morphometric measurements of male and female genitalia and 
<bibRefCitation author="Lukhtanov, V. A. &amp; Sourakov, A. &amp; Zakharov, E. V. &amp; Hebert, P. D. N." pageId="1" pageNumber="26" pagination="1302 - 1310" refId="ref10220" refString="Lukhtanov, V. A., Sourakov, A., Zakharov, E. V. &amp; Hebert, P. D. N. (2009) DNA barcoding Central Asian butterflies: increasing geographical dimension does not significantly reduce the success of species identification. Molecular Ecology Resources, 9, 1302 - 1310. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1755 - 0998.2009.02577. x" type="journal article" year="2009">
Lukhtanov 
<emphasis box="[151,199,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">et al</emphasis>
. (2009)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Leneveu J. &amp; Chichvarkhin, A. &amp; Wahlberg, N." box="[300,538,1843,1869]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" pagination="346 - 361" refId="ref10155" refString="Leneveu J., Chichvarkhin, A. &amp; Wahlberg, N. (2009) Varying rates of diversification in the genus Melitaea (Lepidoptera: Nymphalidae) during the past 20 million years. Biological Journal of the Linnean Society, 97, 346 - 361. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1095 - 8312.2009.01208. x" type="journal article" year="2009">
Leneveu 
<emphasis box="[402,457,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">et al.</emphasis>
(2009)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Toth, J. P. &amp; Bereczki, J. &amp; Varga, Z. &amp; Rota, J. &amp; Sramko, G. &amp; Wahlberg, N." box="[589,784,1843,1869]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" pagination="749 - 757" refId="ref11329" refString="Toth, J. P., Bereczki, J., Varga, Z., Rota, J., Sramko, G. &amp; Wahlberg, N. (2014) Relationships within the Melitaea phoebe species group (Lepidoptera: Nymphalidae): new insights from molecular and morphometric information. Systematic Entomology, 39, 749 - 757. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / syen. 12083" type="journal article" year="2014">
Tóth 
<emphasis box="[648,697,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">et al</emphasis>
. (2014)
</bibRefCitation>
were also unable to separate these species using molecular data. The present authors consider that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alpheraky" authorityYear="1881" box="[599,775,1879,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibina">
<emphasis box="[599,775,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Melitaea sibina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[792,955,1879,1905]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1857,1881]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,560,1833]" captionTargetId="figure-219@4.[151,1436,560,1833]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. 7, Lectotype of Melitaea phoebe sibina Alphéraky, 1881. 8, Melitaea phoebe ab. tatara Krulikovsky, 1891. 9, Lectotype of Melitaea phoebe ornata Christoph, 1893. 10, Lectotype of Melitaea phoebe uralensis Krulikovsky, 1897 (= ufensis Krulikovsky 1902). 11, Lectotype of Melitaea phoebe var. tungusa Herz, 1899. Figs 7, 9, 11 © V.A. Lukhtanov. Figs 8, 10 © expired. A = upperside, B = underside, C = labels on specimen pin." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577635" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577635/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Figs 7A, B, C</figureCitation>
) should be considered as a closely related species separate from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Denis &amp; Schiffermuller" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[406,527,1915,1941]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoebe">
<emphasis box="[406,527,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">M. phoebe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to its significantly different wing pattern, in agreement with 
<bibRefCitation author="Van Oorschot, H. &amp; Coutsis, J. G." pageId="1" pageNumber="26" refId="ref11693" refString="Van Oorschot, H. &amp; Coutsis, J. G. (2014) The genus Melitaea Fabricius, 1807 (Lepidoptera, Nymphalidae, Nymphalinae) Taxonomy and systematics with special reference to the male genitalia. Tshikolovets publications, Pardubice, Czech Republic, 360 pp." type="book" year="2014">van Oorschot &amp; Coutsis (2014: 65)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Korb, S. K." box="[456,647,1950,1977]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" pagination="53 - 60" refId="ref9650" refString="Korb, S. K. (2018) Butterfly fauna of Dzhumagal-Too mountain ridge in Kyrgyzstan (Lepidoptera: Papilionidea and Hesperioidea), Acta Biologica Sibirica, 4 (2), 53 - 60. https: // doi. org / 10.14258 / abs. v 4 i 2.4124" type="journal article" year="2018">Korb (2018: 58)</bibRefCitation>
. As a point of interest the label in Russian (
<figureCitation box="[1159,1251,1951,1977]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1857,1881]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,560,1833]" captionTargetId="figure-219@4.[151,1436,560,1833]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. 7, Lectotype of Melitaea phoebe sibina Alphéraky, 1881. 8, Melitaea phoebe ab. tatara Krulikovsky, 1891. 9, Lectotype of Melitaea phoebe ornata Christoph, 1893. 10, Lectotype of Melitaea phoebe uralensis Krulikovsky, 1897 (= ufensis Krulikovsky 1902). 11, Lectotype of Melitaea phoebe var. tungusa Herz, 1899. Figs 7, 9, 11 © V.A. Lukhtanov. Figs 8, 10 © expired. A = upperside, B = underside, C = labels on specimen pin." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577635" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577635/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Fig. 7C</figureCitation>
): ‘Кол.[лекциЯ] Вел.[икого] Кн.[ЯЗЯ]/ НиколаЯ/ Михайловича’ translates to ‘Collection of Grand Duke Nikolai Mikhailovich’.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577631" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6577631" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577631/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" startId="2.[151,264,1717,1741]" targetBox="[153,1436,200,1692]" targetPageId="2">
